RACE.RACE_TEXT: Bath House Row S. OAKLAWN PARK RACE 11 1 1/8M Dirt CR: 102. Stakes Purse 200000. THREE-YEAR-OLDS. No nomination fee. $1,000 to pass the entry box and $1,000 additional to start. Supplementary nominations may be made by the closing time of entries at a fee of $3,000 which qualifies to start. $200,000 Guaranteed. After paying 1.5% o f original purse to the owners of horses finishing 5th through last, 65% of the remaining purse will be paid to owner(s) of the winner, 20% to second, 10% to third and 5% to fourth. Weight: 124 lbs. Non-winners of a sweepstakes allowed 3 lbs.; Non-win ners of $50,000 allowed 6 lbs. (Maiden and claiming races not considered in allowances). In allowance stakes starting preference will be given to horses that have accumulated the highest earnings. Starters to be named through the entry box by the usualt ime of closing. The Winning Horse will automatically be given an entrance into The Preakness Stakes. The Horse must be nominated to the Triple Crown to be eligible. The Owner of the winner to receive a trophy. Nominations Closed Friday, April 7, 2022
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RED ROUTE ONE broke with the field, fell back and raced unhurried for five furlongs, began to be asked for some run far turn just off the inside, angled out to hit a large seam when gathering momentum into the lane, continued with good resolve past the furlong marker and launched a late surge to be in time at the wire. TAPIT SHOES in the second flight outside, edged closer three wide late in the final turn, drifted in slightly past the furlong marker, bid, late duel, nailed at the wire while between foes. VICTORY FORMATION broke alertly, narrowly set a pressured pace through some legit fractions, shook off nearest pursuer nearing midstretch as the runner up was moving to challenge, found more to duel with that one to the wire, proved stubborn to the end while remaining closest to the inside of the first flight. TWO EAGLES RIVER away well just behind the early pacesetter, pressed that one from the outside, continued on through the second turn and into the lane, faltered the final furlong. INTERLOCK EMPIRE last to leave, trailed well back, angled out four wide turning for home, improved position while not a serious threat. ARISTOCRACY in mid pack and in the two path, continued evenly through the lane in lacking a closing kick. LINE TO GAIN in traffic into the first turn, remained in the first flight for six furlongs, tired in the drive. MAZING MARK fractious in the gate, remained back in lacking a response. POWERFUL forwardly placed for a half, retreated, finished well back. PER RULING #2023-OP-53 FROM THE ARKANSAS RACING COMMISSION, ARISTOCRACY WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM 6th TO UNPLACED DUE TO A POSITIVE TEST.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: NINJA WARRIOR lost footing at the break, was used to move up and contest the issue early, continued to vie along the rail turn, shook clear of the other speed nearing midstretch, maintained daylight to the wire under steady handling. NAVY SEAL behind the pace while saving ground, tipped out a bit to the two path into the lane, advanced two path into the lane, held sway for the place late, no match for the winner. SPEND BENJAMINS broke back, lacked speed, swung out five wide into the lane, finished willingly to be getting to the runner up late. OMAHA RED away in good order, vied up front between horses, weakened the final furlong, caught late for the show. BEST OF GREELEY behind the pace in the second flight in the two path, continued evenly down the lane in lacking a closing kick. RACE DRIVER off the pace while racing outside, four wide into the turn, lacked a closing response. MYSTERY MAN broke alertly, vied up front while three wide for a half, gave way in the drive. BRESLAU lacked speed, in some traffic four wide late backstretch, five wide into the lane, remained back. OCELOT was finished early while off the rail.
